padua, dedicated completely to floras which are deadly and narcotic.";i:6;s:64:"The gardens feature a waterfall, rose garden and cherry orchard.";i:7;s:289:"But inside this beautifully landscaped, contemporary public garden, sits a smaller garden which is famous around the world‚Äî and it is truly extraordinary.it may be beautiful to look at, but it‚Äôs strictly look and don‚Äôt touch in this enchanting piece of land, in which every plant is.";i:8;s:86:"The alnwick garden is contemporary pleasure place which brings joy to millions people.";i:9;s:190:"Alnwick garden the poison garden is the brainchild of jane percy, the duchess of northumberland, whose husband encouraged her to renovate the gardens when they moved into the castle in 1996.";i:10;s:91:"The alnwick poison garden boasts some of the world's most dangerous plants, hence the name.";i:11;s:351:"The alnwick garden is a complex of formal gardens adjacent to alnwick castle in the town of alnwick, northumberland, england.the gardens have a long history under the dukes of northumberland, but fell into disrepair until revived at the turn of the 21st century.the garden now features various themed plantings designed around a central water cascade.";i:12;s:104:"Alnwick garden is one of the most popular tourist destinations in the north of england in its own right.";i:13;s:201:"All reviews water features poison garden rose garden cherry orchard tree house bamboo maze grand cascade change of clothes treehouse restaurant poisonous plants well worth a visit full bloom different.";i:14;s:68:"The poison garden at alwinck castle in the county of northumberland.";i:15;s:68:"We obviously have to maintain the garden, so we have to tend to the.";i:16;s:168:"The gardens are part of the land that surrounds alnwick castle, which fans of harry potter may recognize from the scene where the kids learn how to fly on their brooms.";i:17;s:125:"During the second world war, it was turned over and provided food, as part of the country‚Äôs ‚Äúdig for victory‚Äù campaign.";i:18;s:66:"9 places you never want to go on a vacation poison garden alnwick.";i:19;s:108:"This garden, kept locked behind bars, features a collection of over 100 of the worlds most poisonous plants.";i:20;s:82:"Behind big black gates, the carefully curated garden contains about 100 varieties.";i:21;s:97:"The poison garden slumbers behind black iron gates within the alnwick garden in northern england.";i:22;s:188:"Visitors are encouraged to touch, smell and even nibble a berry or two as they stroll through alnwick castle‚Äôs 26 acres of shrubs, trees and flowers‚Äîuntil they reach the poison garden.";i:23;s:73:"Mudhesh the poison garden of alnwick, the world‚Äôs most dangerous garden";i:24;s:193:"The original garden at alnwick castle in northumberland, england was established in 1750 by the 1st duke of northumberland and landscaped by the celebrated landscape architect capability brown.";i:25;s:159:"By the end of the 19th century, thanks to the efforts of the 4th duke, the garden was at its grandest with acres of flowers, avenues of limes, and yew topiary.";i:26;s:107:"Alnwick garden is open from 10am throughout the year but has different closing times for different seasons.";i:27;s:90:"One of the most fascinating things to do in alnwick gardens is visiting the poison garden.";i:28;s:49:"You can also test your skills in the bamboo maze!";i:29;s:49:"Poison garden curates medicine's medieval roots :";i:30;s:170:"Alnwick castle in northumberland, england, plays host to the small but deadly poison garden‚Äîfilled exclusively with around 100 toxic, intoxicating, and narcotic plants.";i:31;s:102:"Visitors are strictly prohibited from smelling, touching, or tasting any plants, although some people.";i:32;s:90:"Join us, if you dare, as we discover plants that have the power to poison, blind and kill.";i:33;s:151:"Der poison garden von alnwick, inmitten der landschaft von northumberland im nordosten englands gelegen, ist sicher der gef√§hrlichste garten der welt.";i:34;s:94:"‚Äûdiese pflanzen k√∂nnen t√∂ten!‚Äú, steht auf dem eingangstor, daneben prangt ein totenkopf.";i:35;s:96:"The boundaries of the poison garden are kept behind black iron gates, only open on guided tours.";i:36;s:120:"This is one garden where you won't want to pick any flowers for a diy floral arrangement‚Äîunless you have a death wish.";i:37;s:170:"Alnwick castle in northumberland, england, plays host to the small but deadly poison garden‚Äîfilled exclusively with around 100 toxic, intoxicating, and narcotic plants.";i:38;s:57:"The castle itself is the second largest in great britain.";i:39;s:136:"Located at alnwick castle in northumberland, england, this lush, green gated patch is home to over 95 plants, all of which can kill you.";i:40;s:68:"Viking coast and alnwick castle small group day tour from edinburgh.";i:41;s:155:"Alnwick poison garden northumberland england the current duchess of northumberland decided to revamp the gardens poison garden alnwick castle scary places.";i:42;s:154:"The gardens, lying adjacent to the alnwick castle, originally belonged to the dukes of northumberland, the first one being laid down in 1750 and then the.";i:43;s:171:"Situated right next to the alnwick castle in northumberland, england, the alnwick garden was originally established by hugh percy, the 1st duke of northumberland, in 1750.";i:44;s:160:"The poison garden at england‚Äôs alnwick garden is beautiful‚Äîand filled with plants that can kill you by natasha geiling smithsonianmag.com september 22, 2014";i:45;s:247:"The ‚Äúpoison garden‚Äù at england‚Äôs ‚Äúalnwick castle‚Äù is the deadliest garden in the world september 28, 2016 admin 0 comments from deadly nightshade to hemlock, the only way a plant can take root in this garden is if it is lethal to humans.";i:46;s:146:"The alnwick garden plays host to the small but deadly poison garden‚Äîfilled exclusively with around 100 toxic, intoxicating, and narcotic plants.";i:47;s:160:"From the innocent yellow petals of black henbane to the shiny berries of deadly nightshade, the flora of the poison garden comes with warning labels [/caption].";i:48;s:114:"The alnwick poison garden is one of the many public gardens attached to alnwick castle in northumberland, england.";i:49;s:341:"The alnwick poison garden is the most dangerous garden in the world ‚Ä¶ jul 10, 2016 david goran located in the alnwick garden, a complex of formal gardens adjacent to alnwick castle in the town of alnwick, northumberland, england, the poison garden is a deadly attraction that features over 100 plant species of varying degrees of toxicity.";i:50;s:196:"Our 12 acres of meandering and magnificent gardens are home to the world‚Äôs largest tai haku cherry orchard, a grand cascade comprising 120 water jets and the worlds largest treehouse restaurant.";i:51;s:64:"Welcome to the poison garden, the deadliest garden in the world.";}}